'''New York State Route 23''' runs from [[Central New York]] through the [[Catskill Mountains|Catskills]] to the [[Massachusetts]] state line in the [[Berkshire Mountains|Berkshires]]. It crosses the [[Hudson River]] via the [[Rip Van Winkle Bridge]].

Along the way it passes through some very scenic areas of the state.

From the 1960s through the 1980s, map makers used an example of a [[reference marker (New York)|reference marker]] from NY 23 to explain how they work.

==Route description==
Route 23 has three distinct sections: its western third in Central New York and the Leatherstocking region, the middle in the Catskills, and east of the Hudson.

